Seven new firefighters have been recruited to join KwaZulu-Natal’s Working on Fire team in preparation for the winter fire season. The Department of Forestry, Fisheries and Environment’s Working on Fire (WOF) Programme in KwaZulu-Natal conducted a top-up recruitment drive for the Royal Natal team, partnered with the Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife. WOF said a total of seven positions were filled with the recruitment process comprising of an interview, 40 push-ups, sit-ups, and pull-ups, and a 2.4 km run in a set time. Grounds Operations Manager, Smuntumunye Shange, said that the recruits will attend a 25-day vigorous veld and forest firefighting training, which includes advanced firefighting, fire safety, and other specialised skills at the Kishugu Training Academy in Nelspruit. “This top-up recruitment is in preparation for the winter fire season, which begins in June, ensuring the team strength is at full capacity as per veld and forest firefighting Best Operating Procedure,” said Shange.